---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: How committees work together
description: How UCF Faculty Senate committees connect, who they report to, and how recommendations bubble up to the Provost, President, and Board of Trustees.
permalink: /how-it-works/
---
<section class="page-head">
  <h1>How the committees work together</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    UCF's Faculty Senate committees aren't islands. Each one does focused work, then
    forwards recommendations up a chain — through the Senate's Steering Committee, to the
    Provost, President, and ultimately the Board of Trustees. Here's how the pieces fit,
    and where {{ site.college }} aims to have a voice.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="flow" aria-label="Chain of authority">
  <h2 class="sr-only">Chain of authority</h2>
  {% for node in governance.flow %}
    <div class="flow-node{% if loop.last %} flow-node-base{% endif %}">
      <div class="flow-node-title">{{ node.title }}</div>
      <div class="flow-node-note">{{ node.note }}</div>
    </div>
    {% if not loop.last %}
      <div class="flow-arrow" aria-hidden="true">▲ recommendations rise · direction sets ▼</div>
    {% endif %}
  {% endfor %}
</section>

<section>
  <div class="section-head">
    <h2>Committees by domain</h2>
    <span class="muted">Hover a card for the gist · click for full duties</span>
  </div>
  <p class="category-blurb">
    Committees cluster into a handful of domains. Within a cluster they hand work to one
    another and roll up to a shared dean, vice president, or council before reaching the
    Senate. The arrows in each panel show where that cluster ultimately reports.
  </p>

  <div class="cluster-grid">
    {% for cluster in governance.clusters %}
      {% set members = committees.committees | inCluster(committeeDetails, cluster.key) %}
      {% if members | length %}
        <article class="cluster-panel">
          <header class="cluster-head">
            <span class="cluster-icon" aria-hidden="true">{{ cluster.icon }}</span>
            <h3>{{ cluster.label }}</h3>
            <span class="muted">{{ members | length }} committee{{ 's' if members | length != 1 }}</span>
          </header>
          <p class="cluster-blurb">{{ cluster.blurb }}</p>
          <p class="cluster-reports"><span class="cluster-reports-label">Bubbles up to</span> {{ cluster.reportsTo }}</p>
          <ul class="cluster-list">
            {% for committee in members %}
              {% set info = committeeDetails.details[committee.id] %}
              {% set needed = committee.openSeats or 0 %}
              <li class="cluster-item">
                <a class="cluster-item-link" href="{{ ['/committees/', committee.id, '/'] | join | url }}">
                  <span class="cluster-item-name">{{ committee.name }}</span>
                  {% if needed > 0 %}<span class="badge badge-open">{{ needed }} open</span>{% else %}<span class="badge badge-filled">Rep'd</span>{% endif %}
                </a>
                {% if info and info.tldr %}<p class="cluster-item-tldr">{{ info.tldr }}</p>{% endif %}
              </li>
            {% endfor %}
          </ul>
        </article>
      {% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="band">
  <h2>Reading the map</h2>
  <div class="cols-3">
    <div>
      <h3>Committees specialize</h3>
      <p>Each committee owns a narrow slice — one handles graduate appeals, another the academic calendar — so decisions get expert attention before they move.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h3>Work rolls up</h3>
      <p>Recommendations flow to a dean, VP, or council, then to the Faculty Senate's Steering Committee, and on to the Provost, President, and Board of Trustees.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h3>Representation compounds</h3>
      <p>A CECS voice on a committee shapes what rises through the whole chain. Empty seats mean engineering and computer science perspectives go unheard.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <p class="hero-actions">
    <a class="btn" href="{{ '/committees/' | url }}">Browse all committees</a>
    <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="{{ '/signup/' | url }}">Volunteer for a seat</a>
  </p>
</section>

{% include "partials/thank-you-modal.njk" %}
